~ modify_values
starfish: Changing values is super easy!  
starfish: Just assign a new value to an existing key:  
starfish: [br]inventory = {'potions': 3, 'arrows': 15}  
starfish: [br]inventory['potions'] = 5  
starfish: Now potions changed from 3 to 5! Print it to see:  
starfish: [br]print(inventory)  
starfish: Result: {'potions': 5, 'arrows': 15}  
- Can I add new items? => add_items  
- How do I remove items? => remove_items  
- I want to exit => end_dialog

~ add_items
starfish: Adding new items works exactly like modifying!  
starfish: If the key doesn't exist, it gets added automatically:  
starfish: [br]backpack = {'sword': 1, 'shield': 1}  
starfish: [br]backpack['map'] = 1  
starfish: [br]print(backpack)  
starfish: Now: {'sword': 1, 'shield': 1, 'map': 1}  
starfish: [b]Remember:[/b]  
starfish: â€¢ Key EXISTS â†’ changes the value  
starfish: â€¢ Key DOESN'T EXIST â†’ adds new key-value pair  
- How do I remove items? => remove_items  
- Can I check if a key exists? => check_key  
- I want to exit => end_dialog

~ remove_items
starfish: To remove an item, use [b]del[/b]:  
starfish: [br]inventory = {'sword': 1, 'shield': 1, 'potion': 3}  
starfish: [br]del inventory['shield']  
starfish: [br]print(inventory)  
starfish: Now: {'sword': 1, 'potion': 3}  
starfish: To empty the entire dictionary, use [b]clear()[/b]:  
starfish: [br]inventory.clear()  
starfish: Now: {}  
