~ check_key
starfish: Yes! Use the [b]in[/b] keyword:  
starfish: [br]hero = {'health': 100, 'mana': 50}  
starfish: [br]if 'health' in hero:  
starfish: [br]    print("Hero has health!")  
starfish: This checks if the key 'health' exists in the dictionary!  
starfish: You can also check if it doesn't exist:  
starfish: [br]if 'strength' not in hero:  
starfish: [br]    print("No strength stat!")  
